<body>

<div class="container">

  <!-- MASTHEAD -->
  <div class="masthead">
    <div><span class="dot"></span>VOL. IV · SETUP GUIDE · APR 2026</div>
    <div>MACBOOK EDITION · INDIA-SPECIFIC</div>
  </div>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="kicker">Your first recording rig, reverse-engineered and priced in INR</div>
    <h1>
      The <em>MacBook</em><br/>
      YouTube setup,<br/>
      <span class="marker">decoded.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      You asked how to recreate that handwritten-slide aesthetic — the marker fonts, the 3D pie chart, the circular face-cam. Here's the exact toolchain, priced for India, chosen for a working data engineer who has <strong>weekends, not infinite time.</strong>
    </p>
    <div class="meta-row">
      <div class="m"><div class="k">Device</div><div class="v">MacBook (M1 or newer)</div></div>
      <div class="m"><div class="k">Target Cost</div><div class="v">₹0 to ₹30K tiers</div></div>
      <div class="m"><div class="k">Primary Stack</div><div class="v">OBS + Canva + Descript</div></div>
      <div class="m"><div class="k">Aesthetic Match</div><div class="v">~90% of reference video</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- TL;DR -->
  <div class="tldr">
    <div class="tldr-box">
      <p>
        <strong>Start with OBS Studio, Canva Pro, and Descript.</strong> That trio plus your MacBook gets you <strong>90% of the "handwritten slide + face-cam" aesthetic</strong> for under ₹3,000/month all-in. The 3D pie chart in the reference is the giveaway — it's Canva. Everything else (marker fonts, doodle arrows, circular webcam overlay) is standard.
      </p>
      <div class="warning">CapCut is PERMANENTLY BANNED in India since June 2020 — do not build your workflow around it, no matter what random blogs say.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ============================================= -->
  <!-- SECTION 01 — WHAT YOU'RE REPLICATING          -->
  <!-- ============================================= -->
  <section>
    <div class="sh">
      <div class="label">§ 01 — What You're Actually Replicating</div>
      <h2>Reverse-engineering the <em>reference video.</em></h2>
      <p class="lede">The handwritten-blue-marker look has three possible origins, and each implies a different toolchain. Here's what the evidence points to, and why it matters for your setup decisions.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reverse-grid">
      <div class="re-card primary">
        <div class="re-label">Primary Evidence</div>
        <h4>The 3D pie chart is the <em>smoking gun.</em></h4>
        <p>Excalidraw and tldraw don't render 3D charts. GoodNotes users import them as static images. Canva has native pie charts that you can tilt and shadow to achieve exactly this 3D look.</p>
        <p>The marker typography (Permanent Marker / Architects Daughter) in that specific deep blue (#2563EB) on a light background is a classic Canva template.</p>
        <div class="verdict">Verdict: Canva, 95% confidence</div>
      </div>

      <div class="re-card">
        <div class="re-label">Face-cam Overlay</div>
        <h4>The rounded bottom-right <em>webcam circle.</em></h4>
        <p>Standard OBS Studio setup using an Image Mask/Blend filter. A white-circle-on-black PNG applied as an alpha mask turns any rectangular webcam feed into a perfect circle.</p>
        <p>The subtle shadow around it (premium feel) = a second shadow PNG layered underneath. Zero cost, 15-minute setup.</p>
        <div class="verdict">Verdict: OBS + mask PNG</div>
      </div>

      <div class="re-card">
        <div class="re-label">Captions</div>
        <h4>The grey subtitle bar = <em>YouTube auto-captions.</em></h4>
        <p>Those grey-background captions aren't burned into the video — they're YouTube's automatic CC toggle. Nothing to do on your end except enable captions at upload.</p>
        <p>For Hindi/Hinglish accuracy, you'll want to review and edit the auto-transcript before publishing. Descript's Studio Sound + auto-caption workflow handles this cleanly.</p>
        <div class="verdict">Verdict: YouTube native + Descript polish</div>
      </div>

      <div class="re-card">
        <div class="re-label">Recording Method</div>
        <h4>Screen + webcam in <em>one take.</em></h4>
        <p>The creator is running a slideshow (Canva in presentation mode), screen-recording it with OBS, with the webcam composited on top. This is the single most common educational YouTube format in 2026.</p>
        <p>Not a DSLR studio shoot. Not a green screen. Just a MacBook, a mic, and good lighting.</p>
        <div class="verdict">Verdict: OBS scene with 2 sources</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="insight">
      <div class="label">Strategic Insight</div>
      <p>
        <strong>None of the major Hindi/Hinglish data-tech YouTubers use this aesthetic.</strong> Krish Naik, CodeWithHarry, Hitesh Choudhary, Telusko, Apna College — all use "code editor + webcam + occasional PowerPoint" as their visual language. The handwritten Canva-doodle style is a wide-open gap in this niche. Adopt it and you're visually distinct from day one.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================= -->
  <!-- SECTION 02 — THE CORE TOOLCHAIN                -->
  <!-- ============================================= -->
  <section>
    <div class="sh">
      <div class="label">§ 02 — The Core Toolchain</div>
      <h2>Five tools. That's the <span class="marker">whole stack.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede">Ignore the creator-economy noise that recommends 15 apps. For a first-time educational YouTuber on a MacBook, these five cover slide creation, recording, editing, alternative slide style, and polish. Everything else is a distraction until your channel passes 10K subscribers.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="tool-stack">

      <!-- CANVA -->
      <div class="tool canva">
        <div class="tool-head">
          <div class="icon">Cv</div>
          <div class="name">
            <h3>Canva <em>Pro</em></h3>
            <div class="tagline">Primary slide creation · India's favourite</div>
          </div>
          <div class="price paid">
            <div class="amt">₹4,000<span style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted);">/yr</span></div>
            <div class="freq">Pro · Annual</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-body">
          <div class="col">
            <h5>Why it's the right pick</h5>
            <p>Canva's template library, sticker packs, and handwritten-font catalogue match the reference video's aesthetic almost perfectly. The 30-day Pro trial gets you started free.</p>
            <p><strong>Avoid third-party Canva Pro resellers</strong> at ₹299–799/year — they violate ToS and can be deactivated without warning. Catastrophic if your brand lives there.</p>
            <p>Canva for Education is free but K-12 teachers only. YouTube educators don't qualify.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <h5>What to search inside Canva</h5>
            <ul>
              <li>Templates: "Doodle," "Scrapbook," "Sticky Note," "Whiteboard"</li>
              <li>Elements: "doodle arrow," "marker," "scribble," "hand drawn"</li>
              <li>Fonts: Kalam (Devanagari!), Architects Daughter, Permanent Marker, Caveat, Patrick Hand</li>
              <li>Use the Draw tool's Shape Assist for sloppy-but-editable hand-drawn shapes</li>
              <li>3D pie chart workaround: insert standard pie, add drop shadow + perspective tilt</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- OBS -->
      <div class="tool obs">
        <div class="tool-head">
          <div class="icon">◉</div>
          <div class="name">
            <h3>OBS <em>Studio</em></h3>
            <div class="tagline">Recording · Industry standard · Apple Silicon native</div>
          </div>
          <div class="price free">
            <div class="amt">FREE</div>
            <div class="freq">Always</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-body">
          <div class="col">
            <h5>Why it's non-negotiable</h5>
            <p>OBS 32.1.1 (April 2026) has a native Apple Silicon build that outperforms every paid alternative under ₹20K. Everything else is either missing features (QuickTime, iMovie), overpriced (ScreenFlow ₹14K+), wrong-use-case (Riverside, Loom's 5-min cap), or subscription-heavy.</p>
            <p>Grant Screen Recording, Camera, and Microphone permissions in System Settings → Privacy & Security after install.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <h5>Settings that matter for YouTube</h5>
            <ul>
              <li>1920×1080 base + output, <strong>30 fps not 60</strong> (60 wastes space on static slides)</li>
              <li>Apple VT H.264 Hardware Encoder, CBR at 12,000 Kbps</li>
              <li>Record to MKV, remux to MP4 afterward (File → Remux)</li>
              <li>Audio: 48 kHz, 320 Kbps AAC</li>
              <li>Lanczos downscaling for sharpness</li>
              <li>For circular face-cam: Image Mask/Blend filter → white circle PNG</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- DESCRIPT -->
      <div class="tool descript">
        <div class="tool-head">
          <div class="icon">⌨</div>
          <div class="name">
            <h3>Descript <em>(Creator or Edu)</em></h3>
            <div class="tagline">Editing · Text-based · The time-machine for working professionals</div>
          </div>
          <div class="price paid">
            <div class="amt">₹420<span style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted);">/mo</span></div>
            <div class="freq">Edu Plan · $5/mo</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-body">
          <div class="col">
            <h5>Why it's the single biggest unlock</h5>
            <p>Descript treats your video as editable text. Delete a word from the auto-transcript → the frames disappear. <strong>One-click filler word removal</strong> ("um," "uh," "matlab") that would take 40 minutes in Final Cut happens in 15 seconds.</p>
            <p><strong>Studio Sound</strong> cleans laptop-mic audio to near-studio quality with one click. Worth the subscription on its own.</p>
            <p>Creator plan is $24/mo annual (~₹2,000–2,400/mo). Apply for the Education plan at $5/mo if you're teaching technical content — most applications approved.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <h5>Captions for Indian creators</h5>
            <ul>
              <li>Indian-accented English accuracy: 4.6/5 on G2 — excellent</li>
              <li>Hindi: Beta, usable, needs manual pass</li>
              <li>Code-switching Hinglish: the weakest spot. Watch for "matlab" getting flagged as filler</li>
              <li>Always do a manual transcript pass before export</li>
              <li>Built-in recorder captures screen + webcam + mic with auto-sync if you prefer skipping OBS</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- EXCALIDRAW -->
      <div class="tool excalidraw">
        <div class="tool-head">
          <div class="icon">✎</div>
          <div class="name">
            <h3>Excalidraw <em>(alternative)</em></h3>
            <div class="tagline">Technical diagrams · Free · The AI-YouTuber secret weapon</div>
          </div>
          <div class="price free">
            <div class="amt">FREE</div>
            <div class="freq">Plus @ $6/mo</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-body">
          <div class="col">
            <h5>When to use it instead of Canva</h5>
            <p>Excalidraw's signature hand-drawn Virgil/Excalifont aesthetic has become the default for AI/tech YouTubers globally. Genuinely excellent for architecture diagrams, system design, and pipeline explainers.</p>
            <p>The Frames feature converts your infinite canvas into sequential slides — perfect for teaching Kafka/Airflow/DAG diagrams.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <h5>The Hindi catch</h5>
            <ul>
              <li>Excalifont doesn't render Devanagari</li>
              <li>Hindi text falls back to system fonts and loses the hand-drawn feel</li>
              <li><strong>Best strategy</strong>: Excalidraw for English-dominant diagram slides; Canva for bilingual title cards and thumbnails</li>
              <li>Free tier unlimited for solo use, browser-based, no account needed</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- KEYNOTE -->
      <div class="tool keynote">
        <div class="tool-head">
          <div class="icon">K</div>
          <div class="name">
            <h3>Keynote <em>(built-in)</em></h3>
            <div class="tagline">Polish · Title cards · Already on your Mac</div>
          </div>
          <div class="price free">
            <div class="amt">FREE</div>
            <div class="freq">Pre-installed</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-body">
          <div class="col">
            <h5>Use it for these specific things</h5>
            <p>Keynote handles Kalam beautifully once you install the font via Font Book. Magic Move transitions look genuinely premium for intro/outro sequences.</p>
            <p>Weak for the doodle aesthetic (that's Canva's job), but unbeatable for clean title cards, chapter dividers, and animated text reveals.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <h5>The workflow split</h5>
            <ul>
              <li>Canva: core content slides, bilingual layouts, thumbnails</li>
              <li>Excalidraw: technical architecture diagrams</li>
              <li>Keynote: polished title cards, Magic Move animations, chapter markers</li>
              <li>All three export to PNG/MP4, drop into OBS scene, record in one pass</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- CAPCUT DANGER BOX -->
    <div class="danger-box">
      <h4>CapCut — <em>do not use.</em></h4>
      <p>CapCut has been permanently banned in India since June 2020 alongside TikTok and 250+ other ByteDance apps. The ban is still in full force in April 2026. It is not listed on the India App Store or Play Store. The website is geo-blocked. Using it via VPN is legally ambiguous for a creator building a professional brand. Some low-authority blogs falsely claim it's available — <strong>ignore them.</strong> Use Descript, Final Cut Pro, or free DaVinci Resolve instead.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================= -->
  <!-- SECTION 03 — HARDWARE                          -->
  <!-- ============================================= -->
  <section>
    <div class="sh">
      <div class="label">§ 03 — Hardware · India-Priced</div>
      <h2>Fix <em>audio first,</em> everything else second.</h2>
      <p class="lede">The iron law of YouTube: viewers forgive bad video, never bad audio. They close the tab within 10 seconds. Spend your first rupee on a microphone. Everything below is priced from Amazon India and Flipkart in April 2026.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="hw-grid">

      <!-- AUDIO -->
      <div class="hw-category">
        <h4>Audio — the only thing that matters</h4>
        <div class="hw-sub">From ₹800 to ₹29K · pick ONE</div>

        <div class="hw-item pick">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Boya BY-M1 · lavalier</div>
            <div class="item-note hot">What CodeWithHarry started with. Most-used entry mic in Indian YouTube.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹800–1,100</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">FIFINE K669B · USB condenser</div>
            <div class="item-note">Desk-based setup. Plug and play. Great for solo recording.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹3,990</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item pick">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Maono PD200X · USB/XLR dynamic</div>
            <div class="item-note hot">Broadcast quality. Software EQ. Best under ₹10K. Recommended upgrade path.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹9,932</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Rode NT-USB Mini</div>
            <div class="item-note">Solid mid-range option. Cleaner aesthetic than Maono.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹10,999</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Samson Q2U · USB/XLR</div>
            <div class="item-note">Includes clip, stand, windscreen. Podcasting starter pack.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹10,990</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Shure MV7+ · pro</div>
            <div class="item-note">Krish Naik reportedly uses one. Serious-creator territory.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹25,990</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">DJI Mic 2 · wireless</div>
            <div class="item-note">Transformative if you shoot away from desk. Two lavs + receiver.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹24,490</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CAMERA -->
      <div class="hw-category">
        <h4>Camera — your iPhone beats every webcam</h4>
        <div class="hw-sub">Continuity Camera is the game-changer</div>

        <div class="hw-item pick">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">iPhone Continuity Camera · any XR+</div>
            <div class="item-note hot">Beats every webcam under ₹25K. Center Stage, Studio Light, Portrait, Desk View. Wireless. Free if you own an iPhone.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹0</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Belkin MagSafe Continuity Mount</div>
            <div class="item-note">Official mount, clips iPhone to MacBook lid. Third-party alts at ₹500.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹3,500</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">MacBook built-in · M2 or newer</div>
            <div class="item-note">1080p FaceTime HD. Genuinely usable. M4's 12MP Center Stage is "night and day" better.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹0</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Logitech C920 · webcam</div>
            <div class="item-note">Decade-old benchmark for beginners. Only buy if on M1 MacBook with 720p cam.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹5,800–7,500</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Logitech Brio 4K</div>
            <div class="item-note">iPhone still beats it for image quality. Skip unless no iPhone available.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹20,995</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- LIGHTING -->
      <div class="hw-category">
        <h4>Lighting — bigger impact than any camera upgrade</h4>
        <div class="hw-sub">Start with a window, upgrade to a key light</div>

        <div class="hw-item pick">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Window light · 10am–4pm</div>
            <div class="item-note hot">Face a window slightly to your side (not dead-on). Creates shape and shadow. Professional for free.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹0</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Digitek 10" ring light</div>
            <div class="item-note">Entry upgrade. Lights face only.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹1,200</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Digitek 18" ring light</div>
            <div class="item-note">Handles face + background. Better for solo creators.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹2,800</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item pick">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">Godox SL-60W · key light</div>
            <div class="item-note hot">Position 45° off-camera, high, angled down. Textbook Hollywood key light. Bigger difference than any mic or camera upgrade.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹11,000</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">White foam-board reflector</div>
            <div class="item-note">Bounces window light to fill shadows. Upgrade from nothing.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹500</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- AUDIO ROUTING -->
      <div class="hw-category">
        <h4>Software extras — for when you need system audio</h4>
        <div class="hw-sub">Zoom guests, music, system sounds</div>

        <div class="hw-item pick">
          <div>
            <div class="item-name">BlackHole 16ch · free</div>
            <div class="item-note hot">Install via Homebrew: brew install blackhole-16ch. Audio routing for Mac. Sufficient for 95% of creators.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="item-price">₹0</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hw-item">
